    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen reading from pipe, neovim strips carriage return.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```console\n$ printf '\\x0d\\x0a' > file\n$ nvim -b file\n```\n`:%!xxd`\n`:%!xxd -r`\n`:x`\n\n---\n\nThe carriage return will disappear.\n```console\n$ xxd file\n00000000: 0a                                       .\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n```console\n$ xxd file\n00000000: 0d0a                                     ..\n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.2.0388\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux, Linux 6.19.14-arch1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.17.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nArch User Repository (AUR)",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-08T07:54:31Z",
